<subSubSection id="A9083B61F554900F66B488CEC32A46B3" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="8D9F3B0DA77B395A9614D7D72A8B68D1" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Distribution</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8065CC5D4FE0498885B98F4D7F272EF5" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
New records: Struma Valley, Kamenitsa vill., tree traps, 31.05-23.06.2002, 2 w., leg. M. Langourov; East Rhodopes, Meden buk vill., 04.05.2009, 2 q., leg. ALG; South Black Sea coast: Silistar, 28.04.2011, 10 w., leg. ALG; Primorsko, Maslen Nos cape, 25.06.2014, 7 q., 7 m., 10 w., leg. ALG. Detailed occurrence data: 
<bibRefCitation id="67607BF484C1331DD5F92FB15AAE3A70" author="Lapeva-Gjonova, A." journalOrPublisher="Biodiversity Data Journal" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" refId="B7741022" refString="Lapeva-Gjonova, A., Borowiec, L., 2022. New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria. In: Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." title="New and little-known ant species (Hymenoptera, Formicidae) from Bulgaria" volumeTitle="Biodiversity Data Journal. Occurrence dataset." year="2022">Lapeva-Gjonova and Borowiec (2022)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="EF39F6AC159809DB3F78CDC15DE4D58D" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" type="notes">
<paragraph id="0913027EA97F49286001DF150B677FBA" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Notes</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5137B31CE950499E4CBF0BDC79543224" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">
<taxonomicName id="DBE1E7BFD7802DCEE99004F932B1B17E" authorityName="Emery" authorityYear="1908" class="Insecta" family="Formicidae" genus="Tetramorium" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Tetramorium diomedeum" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="diomedeum">
<emphasis id="2C03F33C409414F5D4F67BDD4B6D7E34" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">Tetramorium diomedeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has east Mediterranean distribution-from Italy to the Anatolian part of Turkey (
<bibRefCitation id="E4510902FAD941B5AED8D91B0AC0F9C4" author="Salata, Sebastian" journalOrPublisher="Monographs of the Upper Silesian Museum" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="5 - 296" refId="B7828339" refString="Salata, Sebastian, Borowiec, Lech, Trichas, Apostolos, 2020. Review of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Crete, with keys to species determination and zoogeographical remarks. Monographs of the Upper Silesian Museum 12: 5 - 296" title="Review of ants (Hymenoptera: Formicidae) of Crete, with keys to species determination and zoogeographical remarks" volume="12" year="2020">Salata et al. 2020</bibRefCitation>
). Prior to this study, 
<taxonomicName id="D721CE5657AB4FA735F6FC584661E81F" genus="T." lsidName="T. diomedeum" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" rank="species" species="diomedeum">
<emphasis id="3552DB79F7FC6CA942698874E642E9DD" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658">T. diomedeum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was reported from Bulgaria just once from Ahtopol (Southern Black Sea coast) (
<bibRefCitation id="10726DBAAA7C774D4BDABE2AC662D5B8" author="Csosz, S." journalOrPublisher="Zootaxa" pageId="0" pageNumber="83658" pagination="1 - 29" refId="B7725748" refString="Csosz, S., Schulz, A., 2010. A taxonomic review of the Palaearctic Tetramorium ferox species-complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae). Zootaxa 2401: 1 - 29" title="A taxonomic review of the Palaearctic Tetramorium ferox species-complex (Hymenoptera, Formicidae)" volume="2401" year="2010">
<normalizedToken id="843EBB93FDA613020C583F5343530D4B" originalValue="Csősz">Csosz</normalizedToken>
and Schulz 2010
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
